    • runSAAUsingHeuristic

      public void runSAAUsingHeuristic​(java.lang.String modelName, graph g, simulationRuns simulationResults, java.util.List<org.jgrapht.alg.util.Triple<java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Integer>> k_t0_runs, double r, double p) throws java.lang.Exception
      Solves the sample-average approximation model using a greedy heuristic. See model 4.6 in Lee, Jinho. Stochastic optimization models for rapid detection of viruses in cellphone networks. Diss. 2012.
      Parameters:
      modelName - name of virus spread model (TN11C, RAEPC, etc.)
      g - network graph
      simulationResults - results of simulation as an instance of simulationRuns
      k_t0_runs - list of a 3-tuple of (k, t0, runs), where k is number of honeypots, t0 is simulation time, and runs is number of repetitions of simulation
      r - false negative probability
      p - transmissability probability.
      Throws:
      java.lang.Exception - exception thrown in node labels are negative integers.
